# INSTALL for AcetoScan

- Last modified: tor maj 23, 2019  12:38
- Sign: JN

## Installation

#### Dependencies

Make sure the external dependencies are installed:

1. Cutadapt (v.X.X.X)
2. Vsearch (v.2.13.0)
3. NCBI BLAST+ (v.2.8.1+)
4. R (v.3.5.2), with libraries:
    - phyloseq
    - ggplot2
    - plotly
    - RColorBrewer
    - randomcoloR
    - plyr
    - dplyr

For example, on a Ubuntu-based Linux system, this could be done using:

**Note tor 23 maj 2019:** The versions on Ubuntu's central repositories
are not the latest (cutadapt, vsearch).

TODO: Need to test the pipeline with/without those versions.

    sudo apt install -y \
        cutadapt \
        ncbi-blast+ \
        vsearch \
        libv8-dev \
        r-base \
        r-base-dev \
        r-bioc-phyloseq \
        r-cran-dplyr \
        r-cran-ggplot2 \
        r-cran-plotly \
        r-cran-plyr \
        r-cran-rcolorbrewer

    Rscript -e "install.packages('randomcoloR', dependencies=TRUE, repos='https://ftp.acc.umu.se/mirror/CRAN/')"

If later version of Vsearch is needed, it can be installed from GitHub:

    wget "https://github.com/torognes/vsearch/releases/download/v2.13.1/vsearch-2.13.1-linux-x86_64.tar.gz"
    tar xzf vsearch-2.13.1-linux-x86_64.tar.gz
    sudo cp vsearch-2.13.1-linux-x86_64/bin/vsearch /usr/local/bin/vsearch

#### Scripts

Add the path to folder `AcetoScan/SCRIPTS` to your PATH (or add the scripts in the folder `SCRIPTS` to
your PATH). For example:

    export PATH="/path/to/AcetoScan/SCRIPTS:${PATH}"

#### Blast data base

Make sure you have access to the [AcetoBase]() data base. Can be retrieved by:

        wget "https://www.someserver.se/path/to/ACETOBASE_DB_DIR.tgz"
        tar xvzf ACETOBASE_DB_DIR.tgz

